# CSS Border Styles

---

TheÂ `border-style`Â property specifies what kind of border to display. This property accepts the following values:

- `dotted`Â - Defines a dotted border
- `dashed`Â - Defines a dashed border
- `solid`Â - Defines a solid border
- `double`Â - Defines a double border
- `groove`Â - Defines a 3D grooved border. The effect depends on the border-color value
- `ridge`Â - Defines a 3D ridged border. The effect depends on the border-color value
- `inset`Â - Defines a 3D inset border. The effect depends on the border-color value
- `outset`Â - Defines a 3D outset border. The effect depends on the border-color value
- `none`Â - Defines no border
- `hidden`Â - Defines a hidden border

TheÂ `border-style`Â property can have from one to four values (for the top border, right border, bottom border, and the left border).

